cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.NE 

This paper involves the use of deep learning models to predict hypoxemia using blood oxygenation data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of computational methods to improve clinical decision-making, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves the use of predictive models for medical applications, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
